<theme id="thm209">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Two 16th notes, one quarter note and one 8th note</title>
<tocimage>img209.png</tocimage>

<para>In this lesson a new rhythmic pattern is introduced. This pattern can be written in two
different ways:</para>
<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4 noVisible)
        (n * s g+)(n * s)(n * e l g-)(n * e g+)(n * e g-)(barline)
        (n * s g+)(n * s g-)(n * q)(n * e)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>

<part>
<title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>
<para>Note the difference between the first measure and the others and how they are formed when
putting a tie.</para>
<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4)(n * s g+)(n * s)(n * e g-)(n * e g+)(n * e g-)(barline)
        (n * s g+)(n * s)(n * e l g-)(n * e g+)(n * e g-)(barline)
        (n * s g+)(n * s g-)(n * q)(n * e)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>
</part>

<part>
<title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm209_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear and practise the
introduced rhythmic patterns.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm209_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>

</part>

</theme>

